Peru Stocks: Buenaventura, Panoro, Rio Alto, Volcan Decline

-- B y   J o h n   Q u i g l e y
-- 
2011-10-18T17:32:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-18/peru-stocks-buenaventura-panoro-rio-alto-volcan-decline.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 12:17 p.m. Lima time.  The Lima General Index fell 0.3 percent to 18,659.47. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index retreated 0.5 percent to 2,446.41.  Gold producers fell as the metal declined in  New York  after
a stronger dollar reduced demand for an alternative asset.  Cia. de Minas Buenaventura SAA (BVN PE), the country’s
biggest precious-metals miner, fell 2.5 percent to $39.60.
 Panoro Minerals Ltd. (PML)  , a Canadian copper and gold
exploration company, dropped 4.7 percent to 41 cents.  Rio Alto
Mining Ltd. (RIO)  , a Canadian gold exploration company,
declined 3.1 percent to $2.54.  Copper and zinc companies retreated as the metals fell on
slowing economic growth in  China , the world’s biggest consumer
of industrial metals.  Volcan Cia. Minera SAA (VOLCABC1 PE), Peru’s largest zinc
producer, dropped 2 percent to 2.50 soles, the lowest price on a
closing basis since Oct. 7.  Southern Copper Corp. (SCCO)  , the
nation’s biggest copper producer, shed 1.6 percent to $27.25.  To contact the reporter on this story:
John Quigley in Lima at 
 jquigley8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
